reasoning: Well, this one’s easy for me – I don’t invest in complex technology businesses beyond Apple. Alphabet’s search and advertising platform may have a strong franchise, but it falls outside my Circle of Competence. With no reliable financial or moat data in front of us, I can’t gauge pricing power or management’s capital allocation. I’ve built my record on simple, durable businesses – Coke, See’s Candies, insurance – where I grasp how cash flows and moats work over decades. Without intrinsic‐value calculations or balance‐sheet strength to review, I’d pass. There’s no penalty for saying no, and I’d rather hold cash or add to companies I truly understand than dig into Google without sufficient data.
